Happy 115th to the legendary Bette Davis! Had to go visit her and bring her some flowers. 🌻 What a beautiful day and a gorgeous statue at her final resting place! I hope Bette is on the other side, givin’ ‘em hell! 📽🎞 I love her performance in All About Eve especially, but beyond that, I love that Bette didn’t take any 💩 from anyone, and back in the golden age of Hollywood, when it was extremely rare for a woman in the entertainment business to speak her mind. She is said to have gained a reputation among the industry (men) for being difficult to work with bc she would say when she didn’t like something or give direction. Allegedly that is why her grave says “she did it the hard way”. 💪🏽
She’s an ADDAMS! ⚰️🦇🌹 I had to take photos in front of this spooky Addams Family mural in LA, done by @never1959 📽🎞 Just for funzies! Morticia and Gomez 4 Eva! ❤️⚰️🌹

🌴🪦 I finally went to see the resting place of Anton Yelchin…he was one of my favorite actors. My favorite movies of his are Odd Thomas, Charlie Bartlett, Burying the Ex, and Fright Night…(which is why I left some vampire fangs 🧛🏼‍♂️) What I like most about his grave, is that it actually feels celebratory! It’s beautiful, and the statue of him is so good. He seems to be looking out over a beautiful day everyday, with the water, the fountains, the ducks and geese, and the open sky! There’s also so many mementos and flowers, it’s colorful and he’s obviously loved! ❤️if you’re ever in Hollywood, stop by and visit him! It’s beautiful and scenic, and his final resting place is right alongside Johnny Ramone and Vampira! If the cemetery comes alive at night, I bet it’s a fun party full of talented souls!

♉️ MAY 2 💚 Yesterday was my birthday, and it was a good day! My hip and back hurt, so it was a more relaxed day, but I woke up to @allhailnickyd bringing me a surprise balloon and a black calla Lily in bed! 🪴 then he made me a full breakfast! We took a nice walk at the park with the pup…then hung out and ordered in good food, for lunch, had some big ol birthday cookies 🍪 and we watched Renfield 🧛🏼‍♂️ Which I have been so excited to see, cuz u know I love Nic Cage…I got some super cute gifts, and I got lots of sweet bday wishes from my fam and friends! 👻 I did want to get some cute pictures so we took these, I’ve had years where I don’t have any pictures from that birthday, and not for social media purposes, but just for my own memories, I’m trying to remember to take a couple pics on my birthday. Ya know? Anyway, grateful for a good day, and happy heavenly birthday to my Grandma Esther we were bday twins! May 2nd girlies! 👯‍♀️

🌟Hello Yvonne De Carlo! 🧛🏼‍♀️💚⚰️🦇 I trekked over to see Yvonne’s star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame! Her star ceremony was Feb 8, 1960. 🎉 About 4 years before she starred as Lily Munster. Anywho, it was drizzling and overcast, perfect weather to visit. I thought it was kinda cool, and I show it in one of the videos posted here, that from her star, you can actually see the first place she worked in Hollywood. The Florentine Gardens, which is a white building about a block down. Yvonne danced there in dinner shows before she was discovered and became an actress. Felt like I was walking in some of her Hollywood footsteps! 👻 Also, taking photos on Hollywood Blvd is no easy task! Haha I included the photo of me kneeling and laughing because people just walking right in front of the camera! 😂
Captured in the wild 🏞🖤

One of the things I love about this movie is, it has some of the sexiest females in all of cinema! The scene that features the brides appearing from underneath Jonathan Harker blows my mind every time I see it…and when Monica Bellucci emerges, wheew! 🥵 Lady crush BIG TIME!! I also will NEVER get over the costuming in this movie…Eiko Ishioka created the most beautiful, bizarre costumes, and they literally haunt my dreams. What a feast for our eyes! If you’ve never seen Bram Stoker’s Dracula…do yourself a favor and watch it! …and even if you’ve seen it, go watch it again! 🤌🏻🩸 If you want to see the behind the scenes of this costume, consider joining my subscription area of IG! 🏡🪴AUDREY 👰🏼‍♀️🦷 Day 8 of Harp-O-Ween is the breathy sweet voiced gal who is unlucky in love, Audrey from Little Shop of Horrors! This may be one of the first movies I ever saw…I know every song, and most of the dialogue. And even as a child, I was taken with Audrey. Her tight wiggle dresses, and leopard heels, the blue eyeshadow, her vulnerable cartoony voice…I was in awe…but I didn’t quite grasp the heaviness of what she was going through with men 😓 Thank goodness for Seymour! 💚 I love this movie. The songs, the scenery, and Audrey II “Feed me Seymour!” 🪴🩸This was a costume I have had in mind for years, and I’m so glad I finally got to do it! Thank you to my wig queen @de_oro_wigs for making me this custom wig! I told her I wanted it to be Audrey hair but like an oversized helmet!…and I think she delivered perfectly! 
#halloween #halloweencostume  #costume #littleshopofhorrors #audrey #audrey2 #80s #ellengreene #80smovies

🍒💅🏻JOYCE MONROE 🐩✂️ Day 9 of Harp-O-Ween is the technicolor bombshell cougar we all know and love from Edward Scissorhands! Even though no one in their right mind is rooting for Joyce in this movie, you can’t take your eyes off of her haha! Her color palette, her nails, the ambrosia salad and her sensuality take root in your psyche! 🤌🏻💕 At least it did in mine..even as a kid! I have a very core memory of seeing Joyce’s hand with her long curved metallic peach nails using the door knocker, and it legit gave me a lifelong desire for long nails. 💅🏻 Anyway, I have had this costume floating around in my head for years, and I really had fun being Joyce for a day! 🍑🥗💇🏽‍♀️🚬

🎈♏️HAPPY 46th Birthday Brittany Murphy! 🎉💕✨ I made my way over to do my yearly decorating of her gravestone for her birthday, and it was an experience unlike any other year! I got to meet the dad and brother of the guy buried next to Brittany and Simon, and they were the sweetest people. The dad said that his son was a fan of the movie 8 Mile growing up, and that when his son passed in 2012, and they were looking at plots they saw that one near Brittany was available, and when they saw the dates on her headstone, they felt it was the perfect match! Not only was his son a fan of her movies, but her birthday was his other son’s birthday (the one there helping clean the grave), and her passing away date, is the dad’s birthday! Crazy right?! The dad has been trimming Brittany’s grave anytime he is out taking care of his son’s, and had just the loveliest character and energy! It felt serendipitous, and now anytime I go visit her from now on, I will bring something for his son. 🫶🏼 I also had a vlogger type guy show up while I was decorating and said “hey I need to get a video shot”, and listen, I get it, I go to cemeteries and I share that with my online friends, but I get upset, when people come to a person’s resting place and just put it on camera, don’t leave anything for the person, and don’t even turn the camera off, and just have a real moment paying their respects to that person. I’m only mentioning this, bc I hope to encourage people to be more thoughtful, and to have more respect. 💐 Anyway, HAPPIEST of birthdays to our doll Brittany! I hope y’all will send out a bday wish for her today and maybe watch one of her movies in honor of her birthday! 🌼🪻♏️🩷 #brittanymurphy (also in the video I sound surprised that there’s a lot of burials taking place, which might seem stupid considering it’s a cemetery…but the top hill she’s buried on, has been mostly pretty empty for the past 10 years, so to see 4 or 5 burial tents on one day was a surprise.)

🌸 Hollyhock House 🏡 Took my family to see this absolutely stunning and famous house. Built by Frank Lloyd Wright in 1920 for an oil heiress Aline Barnsdall. I have been dying to visit and see this house in person, and it did not disappoint. Can you believe that the fireplace has a moat?! So extra! I especially loved all the details in the glass windows and the views!! Unbelievable views of the Hollywood sign and the whole house situated so that at the end of the night, you can sit in the living room and the sun sets perfectly outside the window! One of the reasons I wanted to see this house so much, was because it was built with the idea that the home would be in harmony with nature, which combines my love for extra over the top design and glamour with the beauty of nature! Ugh! 🤌🏻💋 the property also has beautiful hollyhock flowers growing all over! Anyway, I geeked out, and took pictures of every light fixture and detail I could, so I can continue to obsess over it. (Also Frank Lloyd Wright’s son Lloyd Wright was also an architect and designed the Sowden House only a few blocks away, and that is allegedly where the Black Dahlia was murdered in 1947) I would equally love to see the interior of that house. It’s stunning…but I believe it’s privately owned. Maybe someday I’ll get an opportunity to go there! ✨ @hollyhockhouse @sowdenhouse
